el":"Prophecies of Hosea","slug":"event-206","score":15}],"links":[{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"rect9laYKg0Xd0Uzg","label":"part of"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recEtv9ql7Hh4XAW4","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"reck8CctXspLk0VZZ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recsU2ZSdzBvDqzgI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"rechyp4HYKyxnaCF1","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recEP3QZ3HUmIkv4Q","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recgAmwf1FZDe8DST","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recIJFRcqI6KbKgXb","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"reci4G5xtsAv4FRwr","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recADz5cMmoTWAEzV","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recU4aisdOryXeQX7","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recJK76HLZSOzxTWW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAVsXYETc2NG2Xo","target":"recekTocE5mIkvDEk","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recA7P1nmU0qEJ3Ya","ref":"Hos.10.1","text":"Israel is an empty vine, he bringeth forth fruit unto himself: according to the multitude of his fruit he hath increased the altars; according to the goodness of his land they have made goodly images.","year":-740},{"id":"recbWSxgbiPYKYw1T","ref":"Hos.10.2","text":"Their heart is divided; now shall they be found faulty: he shall break down their altars, he shall spoil their images.","year":-740},{"id":"recoHFImSxI1hI9P6","ref":"Hos.10.3","text":"For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the LORD; what then should a king do to us?","year":-740},{"id":"recG0rd4hPECbO8uq","ref":"Hos.10.4","text":"They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field.","year":-740},{"id":"recLMSGAPkEvxomLl","ref":"Hos.10.5","text":"The inhabitants of Samaria shall fear because of the calves of Bethaven: for the people thereof shall mourn over it, and the priests thereof that rejoiced on it, for the glory thereof, because it is departed from it.","year":-740},{"id":"recDKZ25tyst0tNqr","ref":"Hos.10.6","text":"It shall be also carried unto Assyria for a present to king Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.","year":-740},{"id":"rec6pzuH6mFWWD59J","ref":"Hos.10.7","text":"As for Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the water.","year":-740},{"id":"recUqjkSuG8djWU2j","ref":"Hos.10.8","text":"The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed: the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.","year":-740}]}
